AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - EUROPE (42): BULGARIA (RUSE) DOMESTIC, WILD
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 22 Aug 2019
Source: Novinite [edited]
https://www.novinite.com/articles/199573/4++New+Outbreaks+of+African+Swine+Fever+Have+Been+Reported+in+Ruse


A total of 4 new outbreaks of African swine fever have been reported in Ruse, Darik News reports. "There are diseased animals in an industrial farm in the village of Karamanovo in the Municipality of Tsenovo. There are 4500 animals raised, and their killing and burial began yesterday [21 Aug 2019]", said Dr Nikolay Nenov of the Regional Food Safety Directorate.

There are also 3 new outbreaks in feral pigs. They are in the villages Prosena, Mechka and Pisanets. So now the [number of] wild boar outbreaks in Ruse [has] become 8.

Two experts from Germany are in the area. They are examining all the affected industrial farms in Northern Bulgaria, and will conduct an epizootic study of where, when and how the virus came in.

A total of 70 440 pigs have been killed so far in Ruse.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The current African swine fever (ASF) event in Bulgaria started on 3 Jul 2019. A previous event, similarly introduced from Romania to northern Bulgaria, was terminated on 30 Sep 2018.

Bulgaria has submitted 4 new follow-up reports during 22 and 23 Aug 2019. A summary of the current event, as of 23 Aug 2019, is accessible with a map at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000031536_20190823_174348.pdf, and details follow:

Total outbreaks = 74 (submitted)
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 133 825 / 539 / 513 / 133 312 / 0
Wild boar / - / 63 / 61 / 2 / 0

The disease has been recently spreading southward in wild boar, approaching the Greek border.

Subscribers may consider accessing an exhaustive report on the severe ecological impact of the current event in Bulgaria, primarily related to the treatment of dead animals, at https://www.tol.org/client/article/28534-bulgaria-swine-fever-asf-farms-economy.html (thanks to Sabine Zentis). - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Ruse, Bulgaria: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6638910,13594.]
